data.text:
Anyone here a fan of SWV (Sisters With Voices)? They were an R&B girl group from the 90's.

http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SWV

Their big hit was Weak:

I like a lot of the 90's New Jack/R&B sound so I bought their Best Of compilation on a whim...

http://www.allmusic.com/album/best-of-swv-mw0000015629

and I was surprised at just how good they sounded on these hits! There's really not a bad song on this compilation. I'll have to pick up their first two proper albums.

Highly recommended if you're into 90's R&B and want to hear something that may have passed under your radar the first time around!

I picked up their first two albums "It's About Time" and "New Beginning" on Amazon Marketplace cheap because they both got good reviews on AllMusic.com.

Well worth the $8 total I spent for both of them. Both are solid throughout.

They apparently released a comeback album in 2012 called I Missed Us that got a very positive review on AllMusic.com.

http://www.allmusic.com/album/i-missed-us-mw0002320271

Also, the title track samples music from The Legend of Zelda of all things (!). It's pretty cool.

The Zelda music:

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IljKQ1BdHKI
